cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.RO

The paper focuses on a traffic simulation using deep reinforcement learning, specifically deep Q-learning network variants and hyperparameter configurations. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The simulation involves multiple agents navigating dense traffic, which relates to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the crowd-sourced hyperparameter tuning of the policy network, which could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
